name: Single Arm Flye
video_url: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in one hand. Extend your arm upward, then lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. Return to the starting position by bringing the dumbbell back up above your chest. Repeat on the other arm.

name: Incline Push-Up
video_url: Perform a push-up with your hands elevated on an incline surface. Keep your body straight and lower your chest towards the incline, then push back up.

name: Weighted Push-Up
video_url: Perform a push-up with additional weight on your back. Ensure proper form and control throughout the movement.

name: Modified Push-Up
video_url: Perform a push-up with your knees on the ground. Keep your body straight and lower your chest towards the ground, then push back up.

name: Single Arm Push-Up
video_url: Perform a push-up with one arm while stabilizing your body. Ensure proper form and control throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
video_url: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back down to the sides of your chest.

name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press
video_url: Lie on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Press the dumbbells upward at an angle, then lower them back down to the sides of your chest.

name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press
video_url: Lie on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Press the dumbbells upward at a downward angle, then lower them back down to the sides of your chest.

name: Alternating Dumbbell Bench Press
video_url: Lie on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand. Press one dumbbell upward while the other stays at the bottom. Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Barbell Bench Press
video_url: Lie on a bench with a barbell. Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended, then lower it back down to the chest.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
video_url: Lie on an incline bench with a barbell. Press the barbell upward at an angle, then lower it back down to the chest.

name: Squat
video_url: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight. Go as low as your flexibility allows, then push through your heels to return to the starting position.
